{
  "texts": [
    "But this contradicts our initial assumption.For part 3, we have already shown that F □ is a possibility frame if F is.",
    "Then since RO(F) = RO(F □), and the set P of admissible propositions is the same in F and F □, F □ is a full possibility frame if F is.To show that F □ satisfies R⇔win, by Fact 2.35 it suffices to show up-R, R-down, R-dense, and R-refinability, the first three of which we have already shown.",
    "For R-refinability, suppose for reductio thatxR □ i y but ∀x ′ ⊑ x ∃x ′′ ⊑ x ′ such that (i) ∀y ′, if x ′′ R □ i y ′ then y ′ ̸ ⊑ y.",
    "It follows that (ii) ∀y ′, if x ′′ R □ i y ′, then y ′ ⊥ y.For otherwise there is a y ′′ ⊑ y ′ with y ′′ ⊑ y, and by R-down, x ′′ R □ i y ′ and y ′′ ⊑ y ′ together imply x ′′ R □ i y ′′, which withy ′′ ⊑ y contradicts (i).",
    "Then since x ′′ R i y ′ implies x ′′ R □ i y ′, (ii) implies (iii) ∀y ′, if x ′′ R i y ′, then y ′ ⊥ y."
  ]
}